Title: The Unlikely Spy
Author: ডেনিয়েল সিলভা
Summary:
"The Unlikely Spy” Back Cover of The Book:

HANDPICKED BY CHURCHILL HIMSELF, HISTORY PROFESSOR ALFRED VICARY IS THE LEAST LIKELY AGENT IN ENGLAND'S ARSENAL. AND THAT MAKES HIM THE PERFECT MAN TO STOP AN UNKNOWN SPY FROM UNCOVERING THE ALLIED BATTLE PLANS FOR D-DAY. BUT THE NAZIS HAVE ALSO CHOSEN THEIR OPERATIVE CAREFULLY. AND SHE HAS DIRECT ORDERS FROM HITLER TO ENSURE GERMAN VICTORY—NO MATTER WHAT.
“BRISKLY SUSPENSEFUL." -- THE NEW YORK TIMES
